Good app, but needs some changes. The audio drops proportionally as the 
bass boost increases. This affects the overall sound quality.

When it works it sounds like it works good but has quite a few flaws. First 
off it shuts off randomly, and then the audio output is suddenly louder 
until I restart it. This happens mid song, no really set time. It also 
defaults to some weird muddy equalizer settings when you open the app, and 
bass boost and virtualizer turned all the way up regardless of my saved 
settings (on pro). I have all battery optimizations off for this which is 
usually the problem with Android equalizers.

One feature I would very much appreciate would be automatic volume 
levelling. On-the-fly playlists and "shuffle" features make a wide variety 
of base volumes, and this app is particularly useful when driving and 
paired with the ICE system, but constantly tweaking the volume behind the 
wheel is *not* a safe way to drive. The additional volume *drop* in all but 
the bass frequency makes this *more* important.

Sound engineer speaking here. Sound is very subjective, but what an eq is supposed to do is not. An equalizer is supposed to respond by boosting the frequency when you move the fader up, not notch every other except the one you try to boost; but I don't blame you guys particularly, every eq I tried on google store acts this way, exept Neutron, but they have only four bands and no bass boost or exciter. Don't get me wrong, this is the best app I found to enhance the bass, but use the bass boost knob, not the graphic. The graphic eq is good only to cut frequencies, NEVER BOOST WITH THEM. Tip: adjust the bass to where you like it with the knob, then cut what's too much with the graphic. Another upgrade would be to add a 125/160hz band, it could be really useful. The virtualiser sounds very good too, widens the stereo image. Good job guys, but don't sit on it and keep upgrading!

In order to get this app working, you must go into Google music settings, and turn the eq on and off, then, go back to the app and turn the equalizer off and on. This will cause the equalizer to work. Also make sure reverb is off. Still turns off after each song.
